extends "base.jade"

block page_title
    |{{this.title}}  &mdash; {{super()}}

block body_class
    |venue

block main

    section#intro
        .background(du-parallax, y="animator")
            .image.bg-cover(ff-bg="{{ this.background }}")
        .overlay
        .main.vcontainer
            .inner
                .container
                    .row.fade-up(in-view)
                        .one-half.column
                            h2 {{ this.title }}
                        .one-half.column
                            {{ this.body.html }}

                            .image-credit
                                {{ this.credit.html }}

    section#location
        .main.vcontainer#map

    section#accommodations
        .background(du-parallax, y="animator")
            .image.bg-cover(ff-bg="/static/images/hotel_bed.jpg")
        .overlay
        .main.vcontainer
            .inner
                .container
                    .row.fade-up(in-view)
                        .one-half.column
                            h2 Accommodation
                        .one-half.column
                            |There are several options for accommodation within walking distance of our venue, Kane Hall. Since we are meeting over a weekend on February 23rd and 24th, you may book farther away from the venue without worrying about entanglement in Seattleâ€™s punishing weekday traffic. Downtown Seattle hotels will be near public transit options, such as #[a(href="https://kingcounty.gov/depts/transportation/metro.aspx") King County] buses and #[a(href="https://www.soundtransit.org/Schedules/Link-light-rail") Link Light Rail], that can transport you to within a few minutes walking distance of Kane Hall. For four star and above accommodations, Bellevue will often be priced lower than Seattle hotels.

    section#hotels
        .background(du-parallax, y="animator")
            .image.bg-cover(ff-bg="/static/images/bedroom_door.jpg")
        .overlay
        .main.vcontainer
            .inner
                .container
                    .row.fade-up(in-view)
                        .one-third.column
                            h3 Graduate Seattle Hotel
                            p This Seattle hotel is pet-friendly and located a 10 minute walk from the Conference venue. Housed in a historic 1930s art deco tower, rooms feature unobstructed views of Seattle. The hotel is one of two towers in the U-district.
                            a(href="https://www.graduatehotels.com/seattle/") Find out more &hellip;
                        .one-third.column
                            h3  Residence Inns by Marriott
                            p This Marriott hotel is located minutes from the University of Washington. The website description promises accommodations with plush beds and pullout sofas. Also available are studio and one-bedroom suites with kitchens that feature full-size appliances and complimentary high-speed Wi-Fi.
                            a(href="https://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/seaud-residence-inn-seattle-university-district/") Find out more &hellip;
                        .one-third.column
                            h3 Watertown Hotel
                            p This hotel is located just west of the Conference venue. Waterton is another pet-friendly hotel. It has a variety of rooms and suites available and offers rooms that are optimized for accessibility.

                            a(href="https://www.staypineapple.com/watertown-hotel-seattle-wa") Find out more &hellip;

append bottom
